      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Sept 23 article on agreement by Sotheby's and Christie's to pay $512 million to settle civil antitrust lawsuit by auction buyers and sellers who contend they were cheated by collusion on fees referred incorrectly to John J Greene, who is federal prosecutor leading separate criminal antitrust probe in New York</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Saturday about an agreement by Sotheby's and Christie's to pay $512 million to settle a civil antitrust lawsuit by auction buyers and sellers who contend that they were cheated by collusion on fees referred incorrectly to John J. Greene, the federal prosecutor who is leading a separate criminal antitrust investigation in New York. He is not the head of the Justice Department's New York antitrust office; the head is Ralph T. Giordano.</p>
      </block>
